{"0":"\u001b[36m[feishu/plugin]\u001b[0m feishu: tool call: exec params={\"command\":\"mkdir -p ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/reflections/2026-03-25 && cat > ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/reflections/2026-03-25/071000000-main-$$-$$.md << 'REFLECTION_EOF'\\n## Context (session background)\\n- Feishu bot stopped responding after `/new` command; messages stuck in queued state due to memory-reflection plugin hook concurrency issue\\n- Root cause: `command:new` hook lacked concurrency protection and hook-level timeout wrapper; multiple concurrent hook executions blocked dispatch pipeline for minutes\\n- Fix: `reflectionInProgressBySession` Map for concurrency guard + `wrapReflectionHook` with 90s timeout\\n- Plugin upgraded from `memory-lancedb-pro@1.1.0-beta.8` to `1.1.0-beta.9`; concurrent protection re-applied after upgrade\\n- Backup directory (`memory-lancedb-pro.bak-1.1.0-beta.8`) caused duplicate plugin id conflict; removed\\n- OpenClaw system commands reference document created on Feishu Docx\\n- Explained fast/think/reasoning/verbose/elevated/activation/deliver command modes in detail\\n- Recommended three-tier mode setup for Feishu: daily (/fast on + /think off), deep (/fast off + /think high), debug (/usage full)\\n\\n## Decisions (durable)\\n- Backup extension directories must be placed outside `~/.openclaw/extensions/` to avoid duplicate plugin id conflicts\\n- Beta.9 upstream changes (new rerank providers, `command:reset` hook) do not conflict with our concurrent protection additions\\n- Feishu Bot Menu support is planned by OpenClaw but not yet implemented; manual Feishu platform configuration is viable workaround\\n- `/reset` shares the same `wrapReflectionHook` protection as `/new` — no separate issues\\n\\n## User model deltas (about the human)\\n- User tests features promptly and makes decisions quickly after understanding tradeoffs\\n- User prefers concise, direct responses without filler\\n- User prefers practical command combos over theoretical explan