ations\\n\\n## Agent model deltas (about the assistant/system)\\n- This session demonstrated that a single `/new` command can trigger 5+ concurrent hook executions, each blocking dispatch for minutes\\n- Confirmed `/reset` hook is protected by the same `wrapReflectionHook` wrapper as `/new`\\n\\n## Lessons & pitfalls (symptom / cause / fix / prevention)\\n- Symptom: Feishu bot non-responsive; messages stuck in queued state Cause: `command:new` hook lacked concurrency guard and hook-level timeout; concurrent executions blocked dispatch for minutes Fix: Added `reflectionInProgressBySession` Map + `wrapReflectionHook` with 90s timeout Prevention: Always add concurrency protection before timeout protection for hook functions\\n\\n## Learning governance candidates (.learnings / promotion / skill extraction)\\n- (none captured)\\n\\n## Open loops / next actions\\n- Verify `/new` hook protection via gateway.log (\\\"skipping duplicate\\\" messages) after future `/new` executions\\n- Confirm feishu bot responsiveness remains stable after fix\\n- User may manually configure Feishu Bot Menu via Feishu Open Platform console\\n\\n## Retrieval tags / keywords)\\n- memory-reflection\\n- command:new\\n- concurrency-protection\\n- hook-timeout\\n- memory-lancedb-pro-beta.9\\n- feishu-queued\\n- wrapReflectionHook\\n- feishu-bot-menu\\n\\n## Invariants\\n- Always place extension backup directories outside `~/.openclaw/extensions/` to avoid duplicate plugin id conflicts\\n- After upgrading a plugin, always verify in-progress Map and timeout wrappers are still present before declaring upgrade complete\\n- Always add concurrency protection before adding timeout protection to hook functions\\n\\n## Derived\\n- This run showed that OpenClaw plugin hooks during session reconstruction can fire multiple times concurrently; a simple in-memory Map guard is sufficient to prevent this class of blocking failure\\nREFLECTION_EOF\\necho \\\"Written successfully\\\"\"} {}","_meta":{"runtime":"node"